This place can be fun to go dancing but that's about it. The drinks are WAY overpriced. $14 to $20 for rail drinks in a small plastic cup. Our bartender was so rude and looked miserable. I always try to be nice, I know they work hard and it can't be the best job. But she was just so unpleasant to order from and outright rude.  The owner offered us free drinks, but when we went to order the bartender asked him and he denied ever saying that to us. I don't expect free things but don't lie to your costumers to try and get them to rack up a huge tab.  Might go back to go dancing but won't be ordering drinks or food from this place ever again.

Visited the location for the first time today. While tickets were free online, brunch and Mimosas were $70 per guest. When asked about seating, my friends and I were given the run-around from the host and bartenders. When finally seated, the manager came and rudely stated "A group has brought this table, you will need to move". When we were seated the bartender who seated us explained that the table was a community table and other parties may possibly be seated with us. I don't appreciate that the messages did not align and the poor manner in which we were addressed by the manager. It's not what she said, but the way in which she said it.  Additionally,  we met a group who had purchased Mimosas but were about to leave. They expressed that they were unable to finish their picture and left it on our table. The bartender rushed to our table, confiscated our drinks, and took the Mimosa picture, as well. AGAIN, the issue is not that she took the drinks, but she failed to have a reasonable conversation with us (patrons who spent over $230) about their policy on sharing Mimosas. She was extremely rude and unprofessional. The customer service was subpar and I won't be patronizing this establishment again.

this is the most expensive brunch in  DC where the food isnt great!! We were there to celebrate my friend 40th birthday.  They only have buffet style food and dont even offer a la carte menu! Let me start with the ridiculous price , $45 for brunch, $25 for mimosas  like seriously?! The buffet was mediocre, the only thing that i like was the waffles and the chicken. I decided to opt out of the mimosas cause i wasn't about to spend over $80 for brunch!  I am only giving two stars because the food is tasteless, the customer service was horrible.. we had a girlfriend that is vegan and we ask the manager if we could get her a plate of kale salad with fruits but she refused and told us she will have to pay full price for the brunch, mind you she ordered the $25 mimosas so its not like she was just there not spending money.  Definitely wouldn't come back for brunch! The only thing this place is good for is if you want to come dance and have a great time!
A must visit, the  brunch menu and atmosphere will make a person become a regular!!!

I went with my friends and we had a couple drinks, we noticed throughout the evening that the bartender charge us extra drinks that we didn’t order. When we checked our bills after the credit card was swiped, without a receive, we noticed that they chargers was extra and we paid 60 dollars for 3 JW black label with coke. When we asked to the bartender, she ignored us and after a couple minutes pretending to be busy making drinks, she came to fix her mistake answering “oh you want the other drink or refund?”... that was our first drink, so we weren’t drunk at all... I can’t imagine how much money they can charge to the people who are drunk!! It’s unfortunate that bartenders take advantage of customers of that way. EVERYONE CHECK YOU BILLS AT THE END PLEASE!!!
